candidate_text:
(Opening Number: "Meet Dr. Wombat")

[Scene: A bustling dental office, with various animal patients waiting to be seen.
What a delightfully quirky request!

(Opening Number: "Wombat Dentist Blues")

(The curtain opens to reveal WOMBAT, a determined and stylish wombat, a dental clinic backdrop)

Wombat:
(singing)
I woke up this mornin', my burrow feelin' tight,
Realized I'd rather drill than dig all night.

Trade in my tunnel vision for a dental chair view,
Gonna fix some molars, and make a brand new you!

I traded my shovel for a dentist's chair,
Now I'm fixin' teeth with flair!

I traded in my shovel for a drill so fine,
Now I'm fixin' teeth with a wombat's shine!

Tradin' in my shovel for a drill and some flair,
Gonna make those teeth shine like the stars up there!

Got a hankerin' for fillings, an' cavities too,
Gonna trade in my shovel for a dental view!

(Dental assistants,ROO and KOALA join on stage)

Roo:
You're leavin' your tunnel, for a dental chair?

(The chorus, A KANGAROO, (K) and ECHIDNA (E) join in)

K: Ah, a wombat with a dream so bright!

(Backup wombats,'the "Dental Diggers" enter, stage left, dancing and singing)

Dental Diggers:
(singing)
He's got a dream, he's got a plan,
To make those teeth shine like the Outback land!

From marsupial molars to koala crowns,
Our wombat dentist is top-notch in town!

(Wombat takes center stage, donning a dentist's coat and hat)

Wombat:
(singing)
Now I'm Dr. Wombat, D.D.S., at your service with flair,
My drill's got the rhythm, my chair's got the care!

Wombat:
(singing)
Now I'm the king of root canals and cleanin's galore,
With fluoride flair, I'll make your smile roar!

(Wombat begins to dance and sing, more energetically)

Wombat:
(singing)
Now my days are filled with fluoride delight,
Polishin' pearls and whitenin' with all my might!

(Wombat re-enters, stage right with a confident stride)

Wombat:
(singing)
My paws may be clumsy, but my skills are grand,
I've mastered the drill and the mirror-in-hand.

(Wombat steps forward, gesturing to the audience)

Wombat:
(singing)
My name is Winston Wombat,'third,
A dental whiz with skills unheard!

(Wombat takes center stage, strutting confidently)

Wombat:
(singing)
My drills'll whir, my x-rays'll gleam,
Patients'll flock from far and wide, it seems!

(Wombat steps forward, proudly displaying dental tools)

Wombat:
(singing)
I'll take on tartar, an' plaque with glee,
My drills will whirl like a didgeridoo spree!

(Wombat takes center stage, surrounded by Dental Diggers)

Wombat:
(singing)
I'm Dr. Wom,'the greatest, you'll find,
My dentistry skills will leave 'em all in line!

(Wombat takes center stage, puts on a stethoscope, A-list celebrity clients start filing in)

Wombat:
(singing)
Now, I'm fixin' fangs for kangaroo queens,
An' whitenin' smiles for wallaby divas unseen!
Crocodile canines?

From bonding to bleaching, the works, I'll do,
The most fashionable fillings,' down under,'they're comin' through!

My drill's buzzin' like a didgeridoo,
Got the Aussie animal elite comin' through!

(Koala client, KOKO enters, yawning)

Koko:
(sleepily) Oh, excuse me... zzz...

Wombat:
(singing)
Don't you worry, Ko-Ko,'t get quite so still,
We'll get that smile of yours shinin' like the Sydney Hills!

(Koala Crooner enters, crooning smoothly)

Koala Crooner:
(singing)
Oh, Dr. Wombat, you're the best,
My teeth were yellow, now they pass the test!

(Kanga-Rita,Enterprises' CEO, KANGA RITA, enters, resplendent in designer dental wear)

Kanga Rita:
(singing)
I need a root canal, stat!

(Kangaroo Queen enters, dramatically flapping her ears)

Kangaroo Queen:
(singing)
Darlin', my enamel was gettin' thin,
But Wombat fixed it with a Bondi Beach grin!

(Clientele includes a fashionable platypus, a charming echidna, and even a certain cute quokka)

Platypus:
(singing)
Oh, wombat doc, you're the best,
My bill's never looked more divine,esque!
